snippet.textDisplay:
Having made up his mind to liberate his beloved planet of the evil race that identified itself as Humans , he descended onto the beautiful dunes of the moonlit desert landscape. But before he could turn to the task in hand , his attention was pulled towards a group of villagers sitting around a campfire nearby. Together the villagers were engaged in an activity .....an activity which he could best describe as creation of a synchoronized  'Noise'  using their voices and a bunch of strange objects .
Never had he ever heard something like this... Enticed & transfixed , he stood there behind the  bush , listening and hoping the ' noise ' never stopped . Hours later, as the group began to disband he approached them and asked what was it that they were doing so far.
The villagers were taken aback by the strange apperance of the 'intruder', but there was no mistaking the earnest honesty in his voice.
"It's something we learnt from our forefathers ....we assemble on some nights trying to keep the tradition alive." 
"But what is it called ? ". 
" We , Sir , call it Music " , quipped a little one from behind his father'
"Music ! Thank you", came the reply. After a few moments of silence he spoke again ," Do me a favor .. Please keep the tradition alive ."

At that moment , God decided that humans deserved a second chance ..... Unsurprisingly we kept the tradition going ever since.
